## Dapr — Distributed Application Runtime

Dapr is a portable, event-driven runtime that implements common microservice building blocks as sidecar APIs. Your app calls `localhost:3500/v1.0/...` and Dapr handles the actual implementation.

```java
// Without Dapr: service directly knows about Kafka, Redis, PostgreSQL
kafkaProducer.send("orders", new OrderEvent(order));
redis.set("user:" + id, user);

// With Dapr: service calls generic APIs
// Dapr sidecar handles the actual broker/store
DaprClient client = new DaprClientBuilder().build();
client.publishEvent("pubsub", "orders", orderEvent).block();
client.saveState("statestore", "user:" + id, user).block();
// Switch Kafka→RabbitMQ or Redis→CosmosDB in config, zero code changes
```

### Dapr Building Blocks:
| Block | What it provides |
|---|---|
| Service invocation | Service discovery + mTLS + retries |
| State management | Key-value store (Redis, CosmosDB, PostgreSQL) |
| Pub/Sub | Event streaming (Kafka, RabbitMQ, Azure Service Bus) |
| Bindings | Input/Output bindings to external systems |
| Secrets | Secret store integration (Vault, K8s Secrets) |
| Distributed lock | Mutex across services |
